Here are some of the most popular and widely-accessible free online Shabbat services and livestream options you can join from anywhere:
üåê Free Online Shabbat Services (Livestream & On-Demand)

1. Sim Shalom (Interactive Online Synagogue)
A very popular online synagogue offering live Friday night Shabbat services with prayerbook visuals and community chat ‚Äî accessible worldwide. Recordings are also available to watch later. 

2. Mishkon Tephilo Livestream
Warm, engaging Kabbalat Shabbat Friday evenings and Shabbat morning services livestreamed on their site and YouTube. You can also join interactive Zoom sessions for community participation with rabbinic leadership. 

3. Stephen Wise Free Synagogue (NY)
Weekly Friday night Shabbat services streamed live at ~6 p.m. EST on their website, Facebook, and YouTube. Saturday morning services are also available. 

4. Temple Shalom Virtual Shabbat
Friday evening Kabbalat Shabbat service livestreamed for free, plus Saturday morning minyan and Torah study via Zoom. 

5. Temple Beth Sholom Virtual Channel
Shabbat livestream services via their Facebook page with free access to digital prayer books for following along. 

6. Congregation Schaarai Zedek (Tampa/Online)
Weekly Shabbat services streamed live on their site and social media ‚Äî helpful if you want a Tampa-area community while still joining online. 

7. Congregation Beth Shalom Live Streams
Friday night and Saturday morning Shabbat services are streamed regularly so you can participate remotely. 

8. Congregation Kol Ami (West Hollywood)
Offers live streaming of Friday night Shabbat services and archived services you can watch when convenient. 




